No sexual dimorphism observed. In life, overall background colour of body silvery, darker toward dorsum and lighter towards belly (

). Thick yellowish midlateral band, often with one to three darker spots. All fins translucent. In preserved specimens, overall background colour of body yellowish, greyish dorsally (

). One to three dark spots on flanks on thick silvery midlateral band; spots fused into mid-lateral line in some specimens, overlying silvery band and starting posterior to operculum. First spot situated anterior to dorsal fin origin, median one below last ray of dorsal fin and last one at caudal fin base. Specimens with more than three spots are rare (
